==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dune
<hw>Dune</hw> <pr>(d⟦umac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[The same word as
<ets>down</ets>: cf. D. <ets>duin</ets>. See <er>Down</er> a bank of
sand.]</ety> <def>A low hill of drifting sand usually formed on the
coats, but often carried far inland by the prevailing winds.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>dun</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Three great rivers, the Rhine, the Meuse, and the Scheldt, had
deposited their slime for ages among the <qex>dunes</qex> or sand banks
heaved up by the ocean around their mouths.</q>
<rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dunfish</ent>⟦br⟧
